<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1580,1931]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[575,693,1832,1858]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks:</emphasis>
Based on molecular data, 
<bibRefCitation author="McMahan, C. D. &amp; Elias, D. J. &amp; Li, Y. &amp; Dominguez-Dominguez, O. &amp; Rodriguez-Machado, S. &amp; Morales-Cabrera, A. &amp; Ramirez, D. &amp; Piller, K. R. &amp; Chakrabarty, P. &amp; Matamoros, W. A." box="[1004,1272,1832,1859]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="970 - 979" refId="ref65119" refString="McMahan, C. D., Elias, D. J., Li, Y., Dominguez-Dominguez, O., Rodriguez-Machado, S., Morales-Cabrera, A., Velasquez- Ramirez, D., Piller, K. R., Chakrabarty, P. &amp; Matamoros, W. A. (2021). Molecular systematics of the Awaous banana complex (River Gobies; Teleostei: Oxudercidae). Journal of Fish Biology, 99 (3), 970 - 979. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 14783" type="journal article" year="2021">
McMahan 
<emphasis box="[1129,1181,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2021)
</bibRefCitation>
suggested the presence of two different species under the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gunther" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[699,894,1868,1894]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Awaous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="transandeanus">
<emphasis box="[699,894,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. transandeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The limit of such species is the northern portion of the Costa Rican Pacific. Morphological studies are necessary to corroborate this.
</paragraph>
